   <center><h1  style="text-align:center; color:#2c3e50; margin-top:0;">Turkish Lentil Soup</h1> 
    <!-- h1 = biggest heading, here it is the recipe name -->

    <p style="text-align:center; color:#555555; margin-bottom:24px;">
      
      Turkish red lentil soup is velvety, comforting, and nutritious!
       So easy to make with lentils, veggies, and spices.
    </p>
    <img src="https://theveganplanetkitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/IMG_3222-1024x768.jpg" width="450px" height="400px" class="w3-border w3-padding" alt="Alps">

    <mark><h2  style="color:#e67e22; border-bottom:2px solid #ffe1c4; padding-bottom:4px;">Ingredients</h2></mark>
    <!-- h2 = smaller heading, for the ingredients section -->

    <ul  style="list-style-type:disc; padding-left:20px; line-height:1.6; color:#333333;">

      <!-- li = list item -->
      <li>2 tablespoons olive oil</li>
      <li>1 medium onion diced</li>
      <li>1 large stalk celery diced</li>
      <li>1 large carrot diced</li>
      <li>1 potato diced</li>
      <li>1 tablespoon red pepper paste</li>
      <li>1 tablespoon tomato paste</li>
      <li>1 teaspoon ground cumin</li>
      <li>1 teaspoon paprika(optional)</li>
      <li>1 teaspoon salt</li>
      <li>1 teaspoon cracked black pepper</li>
      <li>1 cup red lentils</li>
      <li>8 cups water</li>
      <li>1 sprig parsley chopped</li>
      <li>1 lemon cut into wedges</li>
      <li>Sumac and Aleppo pepper for garnish</li>
      </ul>
      

    <h2  style="color:#e67e22; border-bottom:2px solid #ffe1c4; padding-bottom:4px; margin-top:24px;"><b>Method</b></h2>
    <!-- Another h2 for the method steps -->

    <ol style="padding-left:20px; line-height:1.6; color:#333333;">
     
      <li><i>Wash the lentils well. Peel and dice the potatoes. Set aside.</i></li>
      <li></i>Heat a large pan over medium heat and add 2 tbsp olive oil.</i></li>
      <li></i>Add onion, celery, carrot, and a pinch of salt. Cook about 6 minutes until soft and translucent.</i></li>
      <li></i>Stir in red pepper paste, tomato paste, cumin, paprika, salt, and black pepper. Cook 1 minute.</i></li>
      <li></i>Add potatoes, lentils, and water. Bring to a boil, then simmer covered for 20/25 minutes until lentils are soft.</i></li>
      <li></i>Blend the soup until smooth.</i></li>
      <li></i>Add water if too thick.</i></li>
      <li></i>Serve hot with parsley, sumac, Aleppo pepper, and a squeeze of lemon.</i></li>
      
    </ol>
    
